query: Tour Eiffel, Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris
name: Eiffel Tower
review_text:
My Eiffel Tower Experience

As dusk descended upon Paris, painting the sky with hues of pink and orange, I found myself standing in awe at the base of the iconic Eiffel Tower. It was a dream come true, a moment I had longed for since childhood. With each step closer to the towering structure, my excitement grew, fueled by the anticipation of what lay ahead.

As I ascended the wrought iron stairs, the city lights began to twinkle below, casting a magical glow over the landscape. The cool evening breeze whispered secrets of the city as I made my way up, the rhythmic clinking of my footsteps blending with the chatter of fellow travelers.

Reaching the first observation deck, I paused to catch my breath and marveled at the panoramic view that stretched out before me. The River Seine meandered through the heart of Paris like a shimmering ribbon, while historic landmarks such as the Notre-Dame Cathedral and the Louvre Museum stood as silent witnesses to centuries of history.

Continuing my ascent, I finally reached the summit, where the Eiffel Tower proudly reached towards the heavens. Here, surrounded by the stars and the city lights, I felt a sense of exhilaration unlike any other. It was as if I had conquered the world, standing atop this symbol of beauty and resilience.

As the night wore on, I watched in wonder as the city below transformed into a kaleidoscope of colors, the Eiffel Tower itself becoming a beacon of light against the darkness. Couples strolled hand in hand along the Champ de Mars, while boats glided gracefully along the river, their reflections dancing on the water's surface.

But amidst the hustle and bustle of the city below, there was a sense of serenity atop the Eiffel Tower—a feeling of being suspended in time, far removed from the worries of everyday life. It was a moment of pure bliss, one that I wished would last forever.

Eventually, reluctantly, I began my descent, each step taking me further away from the breathtaking views and back to reality. But as I walked away from the Eiffel Tower that night, its image etched into my memory, I knew that I had experienced something truly extraordinary. And though my time atop the iconic landmark had come to an end, the magic of that evening would stay with me forever.

review_text:
Одна из самых известных достопримечательностей не только Франции, а и всего мира. Трудно в современном мире найти человека, который не знает о ее существовании.
Около 8 млн туристов каждый год посещают башню и наслаждаются сбывшейся мечтой, созерцая прекрасные   виды Парижа с верхнего яруса этой достопримечательности.
На протяжении 40 лет башня была самым высоким сооружением в мире, уступив первенство в 1930 году небоскребу в Нью Йорке.
Башню покрывают 20 000 лампочек для эффектной подсветки сооружения.
Также здесь работает 5 лифтов, 2 из которых остались еще с времен постройки.
Цвет, в который окрашена башня, запатентован, и называется "коричневый эйфелевый".
На сегодня, данная локация является абсолютным лидером посещаемости среди платных достопримечательностей и самым фотографируемым объектом в мире.
Добро пожаловать, это незабываемо!

If you want to make the most of your visit to the Eiffel Tower and appreciate its monumental beauty amidst a smaller crowd, try these suggestions:

1) Visit as early as possible. Whether it’s in the lawn in front of the Eiffel Tower or at Esplanade Joseph Wresinski, arrive at dawn if you can – though it is magical to see it illuminated at night too.

2) Book your walking tour tickets ahead of time (to ascend the Eiffel Tower), and if you’re able to, take the stairs and not the elevator up to the first level. You will access it much quicker by stairs than by the elevator.

3) If you’re a big planner, check if any portion of the lawn or tower is closed or fenced off at the time. This can help you map out where you’d like to visit ahead of time.

History
The Eiffel Tower is a famous landmark in Paris, France. It was designed by engineer Gustave Eiffel and his construction company for the 1889 World's Fair. The tower was initially met with skepticism and criticism in the art and architecture community, but it later became one of the most recognizable structures in the world. The Eiffel Tower is 1,063 feet tall and was the tallest man-made structure in the world until the Chrysler Building in New York City was completed in 1930. The tower is made of iron and has three levels. Guests can take the elevators or stairs to different levels to enjoy panoramic views of Paris. Despite initial opposition, the Eiffel Tower quickly became a symbol of Paris and a global icon. Today, it is a major tourist center that attracts millions of tourists every year. It has also served a variety of purposes throughout its history, including as a radio transmission tower and scientific laboratory. The Eiffel Tower has appeared in many films, books and works of art and remains a symbol of French culture and engineering excellence.

query: Tour Eiffel, Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris
name: Eiffel Tower
review_text: THE Paris icon. The historic Eiffel Tower is simply a "must visit" every time you are in Paris. You don't have to go up inside every time but can enjoy this timeless architectural masterpiece from the street too. Tickets cost as much as $60 (US) to go all the way to the top and enjoy a glass of champagne. You can opt for only going to the first or second platform levels as well, and also taking the steps. The elevators are pretty cool and a lot of times the second deck on the tandom elevator is less used. You must take the elevator to the top, 281 meters high, and enjoy spectacular views. You've come all the way to Paris, after all. There are a variety of places to eat .. both of the fancy restaurants require way-in-advance reservations (and are expensive). Buy your entry tickets in advance too. Several other places up inside to get food and drink too. Souvenir shops inside, selling all kinds of stuff, including toothbrushes shaped like the Eiffel Tower (seriously tacky). Be prepared for LONG waits and two or more security checkpoints, so plan accordingly. It can get chilly up there, take a sweater or jacket. Take the time to read the history plaques and displays on the different levels and if you make it all the way to the top, look for the recreation of Eiffel's private office.

The tower itself, an architectural masterpiece. For its time, it truly is a stunning structure. However there are downsides.

Firstly, like everything, it's been commercialised. Everything's at a cost. A cost to get in, to go up, yada yada.

Around the tower, I found it a bit of a dump to be honest. Looked scruffy and untidy in large parts. Big disappointment.

Prepare to be bugged by street sellers and scammers. One "street vendor' was being escorted away by several police, some armed police nearby too. Security is huge so don't be put off.

Some of the nearby streets offer stunning architecture and scenery, others are a bit of a dump!

If you can find yourself a nice bakery, do it. We got belting cakes from one small independent bakery and they were stunning. A tasty end to a Paris visit!

Nearby, some nice walks by the river and other historic landmarks. We'd say we're pleased that we visited to "tick it off" but wouldn't hurry back. Its very cliché.

review_text: It was a great experience. Go all the way to the top of the tower if you’re visiting. Remember to stop at the first level, beautiful view from there. We had champagne 🍾 it’s a little pricey but I loved that it s available for anyone who wants it. It’s a novelty item.

query: Tour Eiffel, Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris
name: Eiffel Tower
review_text: 10 Stars. I have visited the Eiffel Tower on 3 occasions now. This is by far the attractions to see in Paris. Early morning, lunchtime or late at night. You will be in awe!! If you can go up, please do and go all the way to the too. Views are spectacular.  Next time I will do the abseil down!

query: Tour Eiffel, Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris
name: Eiffel Tower
review_text:
Монументальное сооружение, обязательно к посещению. Хотя бы рядом.
В декабре парк вокруг башни похож на какой-то парк типа ВЛКСМ/ЦПКиО и тому подобные с телевышкой посредине.
Много вооруженной охраны, но судя по событиям ноября 2023 года, это не особо помогает.

review_text:

query: Tour Eiffel, Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris
name: Eiffel Tower
review_text: This place puts monument in the word monumental.  Security can be a little tight during peak hours - prepare for a security check to get into the base area, followed by another check if you are taking the elevator up.  First stop has several places to eat as well as a few souvenir shops.  There is also some very cool glass floors to check out the people below.  Second stop has pretty amazing views and a high end restaurant.  Last stop has full stop amazing views and a little champagne center.  The ground level has several places to grab quick food as well as some great history of the tower and it’s builder.

query: Tour Eiffel, Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris
name: Eiffel Tower
review_text:
Wonderful view, but bad management. You must chase the ticket office employees to make sure that whether the tickets for 3rd floor (very top of the tower) run out of. They do never announce it.

Meanwhile recommended to visit at night times.

query: Tour Eiffel, Av. Gustave Eiffel, 75007 Paris
name: Eiffel Tower
review_text:
This was amazing to see! But now, when you get closer, there are lines for taking the elevator or walking up the stairs. Both have to be paid for and you have to go into a severity check point since they’ve had a bomb threat. This takes away from the spectacular structure. But there are great places to see it from afar! Especially at night when it glitters.

We didn’t have the time to go up top, plus we were traveling with a 2 year old. We were in this area for a couple of hours and I think the lines to get up would have been a couple more hours.

Buy tickets ahead of time if you want to get to the top!
